cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the task of generating photographic images from textual descriptions, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel method that involves adversarial objectives, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves image and text processing, which are sub-fields of multimedia (MM) and natural language processing (NLP), respectively, making cs.MM and cs.CL possible sub-categories.
